        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <hi rend="underline">THE BIBLE FAITHFULL TRANSLATED FOR ALL THE WORLD.</hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">CORRES<hi rend="underline">PON</hi>DENCE.</p>
            <p> All communications or remittances of money</p>
            <p>should be addressed to <persName role="author">WILLIAM H. WYCKOFF</persName>,</p>
            <p>Corresponding Secretary, or <persName>C. A. BUCKBEE</persName>, As</p>
            <p>sistant Treasurer, American Bible Union, <placeName>350</placeName></p>
            <p><placeName>Broom Street, New York</placeName>.</p>
            <p> Correspondents should be particular to write,</p>
            <p>very legibly their names, Post-Office Address,</p>
            <p>County and State.</p>
            <p> Periodicals, Minutes of Associations, or State</p>
            <p>Conventions, or other records of public, religious</p>
            <p>and benevolent institutions, in all parts of the</p>
            <p>world, are especially desired to be addressed,</p>
            <p>“Bible Union Reporter, <placeName>New York</placeName>.”</p>
            <p>$30 makes a Life Member; $100 a Life Director.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>American Bible Union Rooms,</p>
            <p><placeName>350 BROOME STREET</placeName>.</p>
            <p><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>March 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi>, 1857</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Philadelphia, Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">At the late<lb/> meeting of our Board, it was unanimously
                agreed<lb/> to allow your claim for $75.00 for reading and cor-<lb/>recting proofs
                of three sets of Hebrew plates of <persName>Job</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your letter on the subject does not<lb/> agree with the earlier
                letters in which the arrange-<lb/>ment was made. According to the latter, you
                would<lb/> really have no claim for more than $25.00. We sup-<lb/>pose that you have
                forgotten the exact forms of expression<lb/> employed in the earlier letters. But we
                took this view<lb/> of the matter. The time was longer than expected, the<lb/>
                trouble greater. The work was satisfactorily done, and<lb/> the compensation is not
                extravagant.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We enclose<del>d</del> to you a draft for<lb/> the balance due to
                you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Very respectfully,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Wm H. Wyckoff</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">Cor. Sec.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Just Published.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">REVISED <hi rend="underline">ENGLISH S</hi>CRIPTURES.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE BOOK OF <persName>JOB</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Has been thoroughly revised by the American Bible Union, and is
                now<lb/> ready for general circulation. It is published in a variety of forms,
                to<lb/> meet the tastes of all classes of readers.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">I.</p>
            <p>QUARTO EDITION—Contains, 1. The Common English Version, the<lb/> Hebrew Text, and the
                Revised Version, with Critical and Philological<lb/> Notes. 2. The Revised Version,
                with Explanatory Notes for the English<lb/> Reader. 3. The Revised Version by
                itself. This is a very large quarto<lb/> Volume, printed on choice paper, and bound
                in muslin. It contains over<lb/> 300 pages. Price, sent by Mail, $1 50.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">II.</p>
            <p>OCTAVO EDITION—Contains the Revised Version in Paragraphs,<lb/> with Marginal
                Readings, for the English Reader. It contains 69 pages.<lb/> Price, sent by mail, in
                paper cover, 35c.; in muslin, 50c.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">III.</p>
            <p>DUODECIMO EDITION—Is printed on a smaller page than the<lb/> Octavo Edition. It
                contains over 100 pages, and will be sent for the<lb/> same prices of the Octavo
                Edition. Paper cover, 35c.; muslin, 50c.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">IV.</p>
            <p>HEBREW AND ENGLISH—This edition is an 18mo. Volume. It<lb/> contains the Revised
                Version in Paragraphs, and the Original Hebrew<lb/> Text, with various Readings, on
                opposite pages. Over 200 pages. Sent by Mail, bound in muslin, 75c.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">V.</p>
            <p>HEBREW—One Volume, 32mo. 146 pages. The Original Hebrew<lb/> Text, with various
                Readings, critically edited for the American Bible<lb/> Union Price, by Mail, bound
                in muslin, 50c.</p>
            <p>______________</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">DISCUSSION ON REVISION OF THE HOLY ORACLES,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">And upon the Objects, Aims, Motives, the Constitution,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Organization, Facilities, and Capacities of the</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">AMERICAN BIBLE UNION FOR REVISION.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">BY TWO “LAYMEN” OF THE REVISION ASSOCIATION AND FIVE
                CLERGYMEN.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The latter specially appointed by a Congress of Ministers of the
                City of <placeName>Louisville</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Price, Postage paid, bound in Paper, . . . 25c.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">   “          “         “        “   in Muslin, . . . 50c.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">   “          “         “        “   extra in Muslin, 60c.</p>
            <p>* All orders for the above publications should be accompanied with<lb/> the money,
                addressed to</p>
            <p>AMERICAN BIBLE UNION, </p>
            <p>
                <emph rend="italics"><placeName>350 Broome Street, New York</placeName>.</emph>
            </p>
            <p>BIBLE REVISION ASSOCIATION,</p>
            <p>
                <emph rend="italics">
                    <placeName>Lousiville, Ky.</placeName>
                </emph>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <hi rend="underline">THE BIBLE FAITHFULLY TRANSLATED FOR ALL THE WORLD.</hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">JUST PUBLISHED,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">1st and 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> THESSALONIANS,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">REVISED,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Uniform with the last Six Books of the New Testament, (already
                issued,)<lb/> containing the Second Epistle of <persName>Peter</persName> to
                Revelation, inclusive.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">IT is sent forth, like all our preliminary revisions, for
                examination by friends,<lb/> and for criticism by scholars; not as a perfect work,
                but in the expectation that<lb/> its imperfections, whatever they may be, may be
                discovered and corrected.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is a beautifully printed work, and can be sent with perfect
                safety, by mail, to<lb/> any part of the <placeName>United States</placeName>. PRICE
                60 CENTS.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Booksellers and Agents, who may be disposed to aid in its
                circulation, will be<lb/> allowed the usual discount.</p>
            <p>—————————————</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Bible Union Monthly.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">THIS work is published monthly, or oftener. Twelve numbers
                constitute a year's<lb/> subscription. It contains the Revised Scriptures, as
                rapidly as they can be prepared<lb/> for general circulation and criticism. The
                object of this publication is to enable all<lb/> who may desire to be kept
                constantly acquainted with the progress of the revision<lb/> enterprise. If every
                pastor and friend will interest himself in the circulation of<lb/> THE MONTHLY, it
                will materially advance the cause of faithful versions, and increase<lb/> the love
                of Bible reading in the Churches of our Lord <persName>Jesus Christ</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Specimen copies will be sent <emph rend="italics">gratis</emph>, to
                any person making the request.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">TERMS.</p>
            <p>A Single Copy, .....................10 cts.</p>
            <p>One Copy, for a Year, (or 12 numbers,) POSTAGE PREPAID,.............$1 00</p>
            <p>Five Copies, <emph rend="italics">to one address</emph>,.............................
                4 00</p>
            <p>Fifteen Copies, <emph rend="italics">to one
                address</emph>........................................ 11 00</p>
            <p>Thirty Copies, <emph rend="italics">to one address</emph>
                ................................. 20 00</p>
            <p>Fifty Copies, <emph rend="italics">to one address</emph>
                ..................................... 30 00</p>
            <p>——————————————-</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Bible Union Quarterly,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">PUBLISHED IN</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>FEBRUARY</date>, <date>MAY</date>, <date>AUGUST</date>,
                AND <date>NOVEMBER</date></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF EACH YEAR.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">THE QUARTERLY contains the transactions of the American Bible Union,
                at its<lb/> Annual Meetings, extracts from correspondence, and other Biblical
                intelligence.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Every Life Member and Life Director, and every subscriber for a Life
                Member or<lb/> Life Directorship, is entitled to receive, GRATIS, a copy of the
                Quarterly.</p>
            <p>————————-</p>
            <p><persName>MILLER &amp; HOLMAN</persName>, Printers and Stereotypers.</p>
